#12301
At the entrance of a Castle~
You have come to the front of a castle, which is somewhat carved into the face
of the mountainside.  It's structuring along the front here is made from stone
different then that of the mountain, so it's obvious that it was built here
upon the mountain as much as carved from it.  There is a man-made pathway
running along the edges of the castle to the east and west, and around the
sides.
~
